cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY

This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to predict the prevalence of influenza using Google Trends data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to gather and analyze the Google Trends data, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with time series data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves statistical analysis, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Statistics and Data Analysis). Finally, the paper involves the use of computational methods to analyze and predict the prevalence of influenza, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
